metadata.description:
A photo session capturing Salvador Dali as he works on "The Temptation of St. Anthony" in his studio.

The Temptation of St. Anthony
A painting by Salvador Dali depicting the story of St. Anthony, a Christian monk who was tempted by demons in the Egyptian desert. Created in 1946, the painting features surreal elements and is considered one of Dali's most important works, exploring themes of religion and the subconscious mind. It is widely regarded as a masterpiece of Surrealist art and has been exhibited in many museums and galleries worldwide.
